description:
The Trojan War begins! The first battle between the Trojans and the Achaeans starts when Iolaus leads the Achaean army to Troy's south bay. This issue features lots of ships, lots of armor, lots of chariots, and lots of blood as the two armies clash.

Achilles faces a gruesome duel to the death with the albino Kyknos, King of Kolonae. Kassandra interrupts the wedding of Hektor and Andromache, screaming her endless warnings of disaster which do no good. And Sarpedon of Lykia at last joins the cast with his army, although he's not referred to by name in this issue.
name: Betrayal 8

description: Along with the arrival of the Utroms on Earth has come the rise of alien hate groups. Even Michelangelo finds himself struggling with the circumstances and trying to determine what the Utrom's true motives are. His identity now public, Michelangelo finds some of the anti-alien hysteria directed towards him!

Hunted by both the police and the anti-alien militias, Michelangelo now finds himself deeply involved with an Utrom named Klag. While evading capture, the unusual duo must try to neutralize the attacks of a group called HAARM - the 'Humans Against Aliens Resistance Movement' - before the world erupts with interplanetary violence!

Final issue! Captain Pike has remained one step ahead of Kirk's machinations so far, but how long can his luck last? And has he lost an ally in Mr. Spock? And on what side is the Enterprise's hidden power player: Leonard McCoy? The final gambit in James T. Kirk's rise to power is played!

When the evil wizard Marten Broadlock pays a visit to Gabrielle, he subtly influences her to kill her own husband, Steven Deschain, ruler of Gilead! But what happens when there is another mysterious figure with the same intentions? Steven will have to use all his might and prowess if he hopes to survive such threats. To make matters worse, his son, the young gunslinger Roland, is lost under the spell cast by looking into the sphere called Maerlyn's Grapefruit. And what he sees was never meant for the eyes of a mortal!
name: Part Three

description: Metallo journeys to the future for the ultimate power source: Kryptonite! But if he destroys Superman, will the Legion's fate unravel, as well? Don't miss the exciting conclusion to this amazing series!
name: Metallo 3000

volume.name: Legion of Super-Heroes in the 31st Century

description:
In the first story, the Majere twins Raistlin and Caramon help a Knight of Solamnia to break a deadly curse, but in doing so they may bring the curse upon themselves. Also in this issue, an outcast halfling named Tanok hunts a group of Templars, but visions of his dark past and a beautiful elven captive threaten to lead him to his doom.

Two epic stories by classic D&D authors in one comic.

  • Dragonlance: Raistlin and the Knight of Solamnia
  • Dark Sun: Hunt's End

Dan and the others try to fight the guards they crashed in on during their escape but the resistance is over. Dan is thrown into the ring with the ultraviolent Wolverine. Now, it's a duel between two live people and Dan's chips are stacked against him. A rescue helicopter comes to aid Moloch. It has also found someone running through the woods...it is Deake. Moloch fights off King Zombie and the Grakken attack but now King Zombie knows where Deake will ultimately be.
name: Rawhead & Bloody Bones

description: Dan distrusts that King Zombie is actually under some spell. As the Voodoo Queen commands King Zombie to destroy the zombies, she suddenly realizes that he was, indeed, faking it and tears her apart. Donna is forced to fight for survival in the motorcycle gang and kills the leader's girlfriend so that she can take her place. Donna, no longer the helpless victim, realizes that she must do anything she can to survive. And the gang may be the only thing to keep her and Percy alive in this zombie world.
name: Gorefest In The Forest

description: A considerable amount of time has now passed. We find that Dan and Joey have found a sizable defended city and decided to stay. Both of them soon establish themselves in the city as Dan takes on the role of a car mechanic and Joey becomes a student. This city is trying to reestablish civilization. Jenny and Marla are Joey and Dan's girlfriends, respectively. The city is attempting to bring a sense of normalcy to the crazed and deadly world.
name: Hole In The Sky

description: King Zombie meets the Demon Lord and we find out that King Zombie serves this Lord. King Zombie is chastised for not capturing Deake fast enough. The city where Dan and Joey are staying witness a sky opening, unaware that it is bringing new demonic recruits to help King Zombie. Many of the townspeople haven't had conflicts with the zombies and doubt some of the stories that Dan and Joey tell them. But not for long.
name: The Path Of Return

description: Dan decides that he and Joey need to leave the city. Conditions are getting worse on the outside and trying to hide within a "normal" city isn't helping, just delaying the inevitable. A new group of humans is introduced. This group is from Michigan. John is the leader and he is joined by a college student, Stacey. Stacey is a woman who realizes that everyone must deal with the new world and resign themselves to that simple fact. Wayne and Albert are two men sharing a motorcycle and coming from Buffalo. They are heading to Traverse City because that's where Albert's parents are. Wayne is just along for the ride...he is a survivor and intends to teach Albert the ways and means of living in this dead world.
name: Emergency Only

description: Joey resists leaving the city but he won't let Dan leave alone. Kirk is a member of a loosely organized faction that refuses to take the overall zombie threat seriously. They hunt down zombies for sport and set them on fire. Kirk and a few others decide to leave the Appalachians because they know that disaster awaits them in this group. Wayne and Albert find themselves forced to watch a family fall to the zombies, realizing they would only get themselves killed if they tried to help.
name: Dead-Killer

description: John must kill one of his own men as he was bitten by a zombie. Kirk finds himself trapped by zombies again and comes across a pilot flying a small plane and manages to join him in escaping. John's men on a hunting party see some movement and they lay an ambush for the zombies that are coming towards them.

Featuring Dark Nebula in a story that would later be re done and embelished for his solo title and solo stories of the Dingo, Flash Damingo and Southern Squadron

Dn Story: Mark Medula discovers his new-found celebrity status has many demands that he couldn't have possibly anticipated. Everyone wants their own slice of The Dark Nebula - on their own terms & to suit their own agendas. Meanwhile the inner war with Cerellus continues to wear away at Mark's very sanity. While the life of a hero is often defined by their challenges & adversaries it appears that The Dark Nebula's career as Australia's super-sensation may well be over before it's barely begun. Or is it?
Because Mark medula ( the Dark Nebula) is already dead there is nothing to hold his soul to the biody when he sleeps. normally he rises to the higher planes, but on this occasion the alien wearlord Cerelus who's soul shares his body drads him down to the demon pits for dudgement. Here Mark first faces one demon but as he decides to escape he ends up facing millions of them. Mark gives in to the dark fire within himallowing hisanger to take control and engulfs all the demons in a fire hotter than anything hell ever dreamed of. Mark wakes in a start realising that this sort of darkness is within him.

Dingo: the full undiluted origin orf Australias scariest hero

Southern Cross and Flash Damingo team up: Flash tries toimpart some of his experience and knowledgeon SC
name: nightmare

description:
Illustrated and written by Karl Bauer.

Has a Jumbo man pin-up in the back cover. Colored by Alex Moore.

This issue is in black-and-white.

Contents:

  • The World of X-Ray: Crimson Tear
  • Captain Daring of the Interplanetary Police Force Battles the Metal Men of Mars

50 pages! A brain-devouring blatant spoof spectacular, right in time for Halloween! After her family is killed and she is taken advantage of by a pack of evil zombie mercenaries, young Dead Sonja is granted sword-wielding zombie superpowers by a mysterious undead Goddess! Vowing to never lay with another zombie man unless defeated in fair zombie combat, Dead Sonja wanders the mythic land of long ago, takin' names and eatin' brains. The biggest zombie party of all-time starts here!
name: Origins: A Dead Sonja Saga

volume.name: Dead Sonja: She Zombie With A Sword

description: Laffin' Gas #6 is part of the Blackthorne 3-D Series (#16).

Giffen and DeMatteis do the Justice League their way! A sister book to Hero Squared, Planetary Brigade stars a group of heroes fronted by Squared's Captain Valor and Grim Knight. Giffen and DeMatteis introduce: Mr. Brilliant - earth has never met a smarter, or more smug, hero! Earth Goddess - by day, she's a sweet, unassuming wallflower, but when the Earth needs her, she turns into a gargantuan guardian of the planet! Purring Pussycat - sweet, sexy... what's she hiding? The Third Eye - spiritual mystic! The Mauve Visitor - strange visitor from another world, or cute little Smurf-like dude? Together, there're in a league all their own! God help us, it could only be from the fevered brains of the "Bwa-Ha-Ha Boys!"

From Dan Parsons, creator of the very popular Harpy comic, comes a brand-new fantasy adventure title! Basement Comics readers unite and check out this great new book! The starving and desperate inhabitants of Earth have at last found a new planet to colonize. One final hope for Humankind's survival. A young world shrouded in the mists of pre-history. A place where evolution and the will of humankind collide in a final, brutal conflict. The beginning of an all-new ongoing series, faithfully rendered in the tradition of the classic fantasy adventure comic!

The Bwa-ha-hilarity continues! Featuring Giffen and DeMatteis doing a full-blown Justice League-styled superteam their way, with characters entirely of their own creation! The Brigade comes together to stop a globe-threatening villain, only to break into smaller sub-divided teams on sub-missions fighting smaller threats. Piecing together a larger puzzle, in this issue everything begins to come together and make sense, as the Planetary Brigade begins to answer this question: why won't Harry Cutter die? Bonus: a pin-up by the legendary Silver Age great, Sal Buscema!

Wanted for high treason! Renegade astronaut Captain Hawkins is tracked into the uncharted prehistoric wilderness of Terra I! Even with the aid of his beautiful native companion, Jakella, Hawkins cannot escape the ruthless pursuit of the Colonial Militia and its army of Attack Droids. At last, captured and imprisoned by the Planetary Authority, Hawkins is placed aboard a prison ship and rocketed back to his homeworld to face a challenge even he cannot hope to survive: a life sentence, stranded on the dark and decaying world known as Old Earth!
